Tanker, Dry Bulk Fleets Are Worth $309.7 Billion, Seasure Says

-- B y   A l a r i c   N i g h t i n g a l e
-- 
2011-05-13T11:48:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/tanker-dry-bulk-fleets-are-worth-309-7-billion-seasure-says.html
The combined global fleet of oil
tankers and dry-bulk commodity carriers is worth $309.7 billion,
Seasure Shipping Ltd., a London-based shipbroker said in a
statement today.  The figure was the first such estimate produced by
vesselsvalue.com, a website Seasure built to provide automated
ship evaluations. Bulkers are worth $166.6 billion and tankers
$143.1 billion, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaric Nightingale in London at 
 anightingal1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Wallace at 
 swallace6@bloomberg.net  